1
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,400
STRONG BLEACHING POWDER

2
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,400
Qiao.

3
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:55,560
The real owner of this house
is you, isn't it?

4
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,920
Mr. He, you're confused.

5
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:13,440
This was my former employer's house.

6
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,640
I only lived here before.

7
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:17,760
How could I be the owner?

8
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:20,640
Then who was your former employer?

9
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:24,280
Many people in Yuanlongli know that.

10
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:26,440
I'm asking about the real employer.

11
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:29,200
The son of Yao Baiyuan,

12
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,600
Yao Xincheng.

13
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:46,520
You should know
who I'm talking about, right?

14
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:49,400
In 1996,

15
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:52,880
Yao Xincheng bought this apartment
under the name of Yao Baiyuan.

16
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,320
In 2002,

17
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,320
he asked you to sell it.

18
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:59,280
Then in 2003,

19
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:01,480
you used Yao Xincheng's name

20
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,000
to buy it back again,

21
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,960
but it was never transferred.

22
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,160
Why?

23
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,840
Because you didn't want
your own name to appear

24
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:13,360
on the owner's list.

25
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,640
You smashed this place up

26
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:18,360
and left it vacant for 12 years.

27
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,680
You were worried
that if anyone else lived here,

28
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:22,320
you'd never feel at ease.

29
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:23,960
Am I right?

30
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:25,760
Yes.

31
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:29,480
I'll never be at ease.

32
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,800
In this apartment,

33
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:35,040
Yao Baiyuan abused me.

34
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:37,560
Wu Shanlong peeped at me.

35
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:40,000
I hate this place to my core.

36
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:41,560
I wanted to vent.

37
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:43,400
I wanted to destroy it.

38
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:46,760
- Is that wrong?
- You can hate people,

39
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:48,560
but you can't kill them.

40
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,480
Qiao Suqing,

41
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,880
you are suspected of intentional murder

42
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:04,480
in accordance with Article 117

43
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:06,280
of the Criminal Procedure Law
of the People's Republic of China.

44
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:09,160
Please come with us to the police station
for questioning.

45
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,760
SUMMONS

46
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,240
Who did I kill?

47
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:15,120
You are suspected
of kidnapping and murdering

48
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:17,320
Xu Zhihong and Xu Meng.

49
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:33,760
DEMOLITION

50
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,960
Xiaohe,

51
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:33,040
I didn't expect
you'd be the one questioning me.

52
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:34,680
I thought

53
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:37,240
you should've recused yourself,

54
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:38,800
considering how well we know each other.

55
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:50,040
Qiao Suqing,

56
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:51,680
listen carefully.

57
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:54,840
<i>In this room,</i>
<i>there is only one relationship</i>

58
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:55,880
<i>between two people sitting face to face.</i>

59
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:58,160
That is a police officer
and a criminal suspect.

60
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,480
And a suspect has only one way
to address an officer.

61
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:03,280
That is Officer.

62
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:05,120
Alright.

63
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:06,760
Officer He.

64
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,480
Qiao Suqing,

65
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,000
now tell the truth.

66
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:13,760
How did you kill Xu Meng and her father?

67
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:16,800
Officer He,

68
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:19,280
I've never harmed anyone,

69
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,760
let alone killed anyone.

70
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:25,720
I don't know why Mr. He
and you would suspect me.

71
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:29,080
If not for this evidence,

72
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,640
I wouldn't believe

73
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,640
that the Qiao Suqing
sitting in front of me

74
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,800
would be suspected of murder.

75
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,320
But evidence is evidence.

76
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:39,000
It doesn't lie,

77
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:42,080
much less deceive people on purpose
for all these years.

78
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:45,040
Officer He,

79
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,640
I don't know what evidence you have,

80
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,000
but there must be some misunderstanding.

81
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:56,160
Since you say there's a misunderstanding,

82
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,880
then cooperate with us

83
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:01,120
and answer my questions truthfully.

84
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:06,680
Ask away.

85
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:10,160
While you lived
in No. 415 at New York Block,

86
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:12,360
was your home ever burglarized?

87
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:17,520
- No.
- Are you sure nothing was stolen?

88
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:19,720
I am.

89
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:26,840
Do you know Yao Xincheng?

90
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,400
Yes.

91
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,560
On December 29th, 1996,

92
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:32,960
did Yao Xincheng give you this dress?

93
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,720
I don't remember.

94
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:43,880
Did Mr. Yao tell you

95
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:45,520
he gave me that dress?

96
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,160
Answer my question.

97
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,040
If Mr. Yao said he gave it,

98
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,560
then I suppose he did.

99
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:56,760
To make up for what his father did to me,

100
00:08:57,720 --> 00:08:59,480
he gave me many clothes.

101
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:03,120
But I never wore a single one.

102
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:05,760
Putting them on

103
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:10,360
would only remind me
of what his father did to me.

104
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:13,080
Why was the dress Yao Xincheng gave you

105
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:14,760
hanging in Xu Meng's home?

106
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:20,800
That dress was a classic style
from the Bowls.

107
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:23,280
A lot of people bought it back then.

108
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,160
How can you prove

109
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:29,080
the one in Xu Meng's house
was the one he gave me?

110
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:31,400
Every question I ask is well-founded.

111
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:33,440
You only need to answer truthfully.

112
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:36,520
Why did the dress Yao Xincheng gave you

113
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:39,520
appear in Xu Meng's house?

114
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:45,760
Officer He,

115
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:48,120
my house was never robbed.

116
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:51,120
Any clothes Yao Xincheng gave me,

117
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:54,280
I took them
to the wholesale clothing market

118
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:56,240
and sold them cheaply
to small shop owners.

119
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:59,760
As for who they resold them to,

120
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,360
I wouldn't know.

121
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,520
Qiao Suqing,

122
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:10,240
on July 2nd, 1997, where were you?

123
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,160
I don't remember.

124
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,640
All I remember

125
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:18,680
is that during that time,
I stayed home every day studying

126
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:20,120
and preparing for the Adult Gaokao.

127
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:26,640
Officer He, you came to my house then.

128
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:37,840
You asked me what the Adult Gaokao was.

129
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,400
We promised each other

130
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:51,760
we'd both become top students.

131
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:54,000
Qiao Suqing, don't dodge the question.

132
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:55,960
Sorry.

133
00:10:57,760 --> 00:10:59,960
Maybe too much time has passed.

134
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:05,480
I can only remember the good memories.

135
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,760
Dad, I really like Ms. Qiao.

136
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,600
Can you ask Uncle Ran
to bring me here often?

137
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:13,160
From the first time I met you,

138
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,840
I felt like you'd become family.

139
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,920
Since you said

140
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,680
you hated remembering
the harm Yao Baiyuan did to you

141
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:34,160
and you refused to wear
the clothes Yao Xincheng bought you,

142
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:36,760
then why did you stay
in their apartment for so many years

143
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,920
after Yao Baiyuan died,

144
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:40,360
even when people called you a mistress?

145
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,160
I had no choice.

146
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:45,080
I had nowhere to go.

147
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:47,880
If I hadn't stayed there,
I would've ended up on the streets.

148
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,360
More than my dignity,

149
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:53,160
I needed to survive.

150
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:05,080
Do you recognize this pair of heels?

151
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:18,360
No.

152
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:21,840
They appear to be a pair of blue heels.

153
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:25,720
<i>But they were covered in blue leather.</i>

154
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:29,160
They were supposed to be red heels.

155
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,520
Now that I've said this much,

156
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:35,720
you should recognize it.

157
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,160
Fine.

158
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:42,480
If you don't know the heels,

159
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:45,360
there's someone you definitely know.

160
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,640
<i>My name is Zhu Ziqiang.</i>

161
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:57,560
<i>I used to work</i>
<i>as Mr. Yao Xincheng's driver.</i>

162
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:59,640
In the summer of 2002,

163
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:01,480
Qiao Suqing came to me.

164
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:05,000
<i>She gave me a pair</i>
<i>of Double Fish brand red heels</i>

165
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,240
<i>and 2,000 yuan.</i>

166
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:09,360
She told me to go to a place
called Pingzhao County

167
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:12,480
and find a shoemaker named Mr. Lu.

168
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:17,480
She wanted me to have those red heels
covered with blue leather.

169
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:19,960
<i>Qiao Suqing specifically warned me</i>

170
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,480
<i>that when I went to see Mr. Lu,</i>

171
00:13:21,560 --> 00:13:23,120
<i>I had to cover myself up completely.</i>

172
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,560
<i>Wear a hat or sunglasses.</i>

173
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,440
Qiao Suqing,

174
00:13:30,520 --> 00:13:31,960
why did you do that?

175
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:35,000
And why were those altered heels
found in Wu Shanlong's home?

176
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:38,640
You can tell us now

177
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:41,000
how you killed Xu Meng and her father

178
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:43,080
and framed Wu Shanlong.

179
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:51,000
I did ask Yao Xincheng's driver

180
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,920
to have the red heels altered.

181
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:59,920
But later, Wu Shanlong stole them.

182
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:01,720
He had a fetish.

183
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:03,600
He stole women's clothes
from the building.

184
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:05,680
I asked you that in my first question.

185
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,760
You said nothing
had been stolen from your home.

186
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:10,200
Can't I forget something?

187
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:13,960
Can a pair of heels prove I'm a murderer?

188
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:16,800
I… I don't even know
Xu Meng and her father.

189
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:19,000
I had nothing to do with them.

190
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:20,920
Why… Why would I kill them?

191
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:28,880
Who is Fang Xiuhong to you?

192
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:32,240
Qiao Suqing,

193
00:14:32,760 --> 00:14:34,280
answer my question.

194
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,520
Who is Fang Xiuhong to you?

195
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:45,280
She was my mother.

196
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:49,000
She was one of the victims
of the August 24th Mount Wu Accident.

197
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:50,600
Right?

198
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:57,480
XU ZHIHONG, XU MENG

199
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:04,880
FANG XIUHONG, QIAO SUQING

200
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,680
Xu Meng and Xu Zhihong

201
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:09,760
were among the victims
of that accident too.

202
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:11,480
Yet you claimed
you had nothing to do with them?

203
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:12,920
Xu Meng deserved to die!

204
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,200
She deserved it!

205
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:30,880
<i>In August 1995, my mother and I</i>

206
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:33,800
<i>signed up for a tour group.</i>

207
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:37,200
Alright, everyone. Let's do a roll call.

208
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:40,320
- Wang Zusheng.
- Here.

209
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,240
- Qiao Suqing.
- Here.

210
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:44,720
Fang Xiuhong.

211
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:46,160
Here.

212
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,680
- Xu Zhihong.
- Over here.

213
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:52,200
- Xu Meng.
- Here.

214
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:53,800
Be careful.

215
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:59,120
Stay close together.

216
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:05,160
You can slow down a little.

217
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:08,600
Well. Everyone in the back, keep up.

218
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:10,800
Steady yourselves.

219
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:12,680
Hold on to the rope beside you.

220
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:13,760
Be careful.

221
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,840
Those taking photos,
once you're done, catch up quickly.

222
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:17,760
Meng, move this way a bit.

223
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:18,680
Closer this way.

224
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:19,720
Yes.

225
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:22,880
KUNPENG TRAVEL AGENCY

226
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,280
Your cap.

227
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,520
<i>Everyone,</i>

228
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:44,560
<i>watch your footing.</i>

229
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:45,800
<i>The trail is slippery.</i>

230
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:47,760
<i>Be mindful of both sides.</i>

231
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,520
<i>Mount Wu not only has beautiful scenery,</i>

232
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:52,800
<i>but also over a hundred species of plants.</i>

233
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,280
I tripped.

234
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:56,480
- Are you alright?
- Be careful.

235
00:16:57,520 --> 00:16:59,040
Why is the fog so thick?

236
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:00,280
We can't even see the road.

237
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:02,000
Exactly. My wife fell.

238
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,880
<i>Everyone, don't panic.</i>

239
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:05,960
<i>This kind of weather</i>
<i>is very common on Mount Wu.</i>

240
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:08,400
<i>The heavy fog will clear soon.</i>

241
00:17:08,480 --> 00:17:10,880
<i>How about this?</i>
<i>Hold hands with people around you.</i>

242
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,480
<i>Don't get separated.</i>

243
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:14,079
<i>Follow me. Alright?</i>

244
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:14,760
KUNPENG TRAVEL AGENCY

245
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:17,400
- Hang in there.
- Take it slow.

246
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:18,599
Walk slowly.

247
00:17:23,560 --> 00:17:24,440
Walk slowly.

248
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,200
I…

249
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:30,600
- I can't breathe.
- Come.

250
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:32,520
Rest here for a bit.

251
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:33,680
Sit down.

252
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,480
Why are you sitting down?

253
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:44,440
Hurry up. Don't hold us back.

254
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:45,520
I can't walk anymore.

255
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:48,080
You see,

256
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:49,640
we really can't stay here.

257
00:17:49,720 --> 00:17:51,160
It'll be dark soon.

258
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:52,200
We'll freeze to death if we stay here.

259
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:55,280
Can't you be considerate
and wait a little?

260
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:57,040
You can't drag us down with you.

261
00:17:57,120 --> 00:17:58,800
Why bother with them? Let's just go.

262
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:00,520
- Go.
- Let's leave.

263
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:03,640
You rest a bit. Catch up quickly.

264
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:10,200
Qing.

265
00:18:10,280 --> 00:18:11,360
Qing.

266
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:12,520
Qing.

267
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:13,680
Qing.

268
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:14,800
Qing.

269
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:25,920
Mom.

270
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:29,840
Mom.

271
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:31,760
Mom.

272
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:39,200
- Excuse me. Where's my mom?
- Don't… Don't come near us.

273
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:43,800
I'm warning you.

274
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:45,240
Don't…

275
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:46,560
Don't try anything.

276
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:48,400
What are you talking about?

277
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:50,520
Where… Where's my mom?

278
00:18:51,160 --> 00:18:52,720
You're worse than an animal!

279
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,480
You have no conscience!

280
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:57,080
You… What are you talking about?

281
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:59,120
I'm just asking where my mom is.

282
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,720
Stop pretending.

283
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:03,680
Before you passed out, you went crazy

284
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:05,520
trying to tear the clothes
off my dad and me.

285
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:06,360
We refused,

286
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:08,320
and you nearly pushed my dad
off the cliff.

287
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,080
His leg was broken.

288
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,080
Then…

289
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:13,200
Then you went to grab your mom's clothes.

290
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:14,920
Your mom was frozen stiff.

291
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,280
She wouldn't give them to you,

292
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:18,120
and you pushed her off the cliff.

293
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:22,960
No. That can't be true.

294
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:33,640
Mom!

295
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:35,680
Mom!

296
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,040
Where are you, Mom?

297
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:40,400
Mom!

298
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:42,000
Mom!

299
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,640
Mom!

300
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:57,360
I passed out from the cold again

301
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,480
at the bottom of the cliff.

302
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:04,640
<i>When I woke up,</i>

303
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:07,240
<i>I found myself in the rescue vehicle.</i>

304
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:10,720
They found my mother's body

305
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:13,200
at the bottom of the cliff.

306
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:35,200
After the incident,

307
00:20:36,760 --> 00:20:38,320
my aunt took me in.

308
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:43,840
<i>I ate, lived, and worked</i>

309
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,480
<i>at her restaurant.</i>

310
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:48,920
We got along well at first.

311
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:53,440
But after the compensation money came in,

312
00:20:55,720 --> 00:20:56,960
everything changed.

313
00:20:57,920 --> 00:21:01,200
You jinx! Are you blind?

314
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:03,240
There, there. Don't cry.

315
00:21:03,320 --> 00:21:04,400
You killed my sister,
and that still wasn't enough?

316
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,560
Stay away from my granddaughter.

317
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,040
Rotten luck.

318
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:09,280
Meeting you was the worst thing
that ever happened to me.

319
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:17,560
Qing, are you tired?

320
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:21,360
Look at you. Your clothes are soaked.

321
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:22,280
I'll help you change.

322
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:23,400
You might catch a cold.

323
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:24,480
Catching a cold is serious.

324
00:21:24,560 --> 00:21:25,840
Hurry up.

325
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:26,800
You shameless flirt.

326
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:29,440
I'll beat you to death. You witch!

327
00:21:29,520 --> 00:21:31,240
Shameless flirt! Shameless!

328
00:21:31,320 --> 00:21:32,360
Trash!

329
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:33,240
Flirt!

330
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:35,080
Witch! Witch!

331
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:43,040
Qing, come here.

332
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:44,240
Leave the dishes for now.

333
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:46,240
Come. I have something to tell you.

334
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:47,600
Great news.

335
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:49,640
You've worked hard.

336
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:52,800
I've found you a good place.

337
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:59,720
She said she found me a good place,

338
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:01,400
but really, she took someone's money

339
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:05,320
and sold me away to be
a servant in another town.

340
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:11,120
When I first met Yao Xincheng,

341
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:15,200
I thought

342
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:18,800
he looked like
a refined and successful man.

343
00:22:24,560 --> 00:22:25,800
<i>I thought to myself,</i>

344
00:22:26,480 --> 00:22:28,160
<i>my luck wasn't that bad after all.</i>

345
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:30,720
Serving someone like him

346
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:36,000
had to be a thousand times better
than staying at my aunt's home.

347
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:40,080
NEW YORK BLOCK

348
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:47,640
But I was completely wrong.

349
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,640
<i>Yao Xincheng brought me to Yuanlongli</i>

350
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:57,480
<i>to look after his father.</i>

351
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:21,800
<i>From the day I met Yao Baiyuan,</i>

352
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:23,640
<i>I finally understood</i>

353
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:27,040
<i>what a true living hell was.</i>

354
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:41,440
NEW YORK BLOCK

355
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:42,360
Mr. Yao,

356
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:44,840
I really can't do this anymore.

357
00:23:46,320 --> 00:23:47,680
I'll find a way to pay back

358
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:49,960
however much you paid my aunt.

359
00:23:57,080 --> 00:23:59,080
- Wait outside.
- Alright.

360
00:24:05,760 --> 00:24:06,760
Qiao,

361
00:24:06,840 --> 00:24:09,160
I apologize on behalf of my dad.

362
00:24:10,040 --> 00:24:11,240
Given his current condition,

363
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:12,920
I really can't find anyone else.

364
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:14,400
I can raise your pay.

365
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:16,320
As much as you want. Is that alright?

366
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:23,600
I went to Weiyang Mall earlier today

367
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:24,760
and picked out some gifts for you.

368
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:26,040
Here. Take it.

369
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:29,040
Mr. Yao, I really can't do this anymore.

370
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:41,760
Five years.

371
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:44,440
If you can take care of my dad
for five full years,

372
00:24:45,280 --> 00:24:47,000
I'll transfer the apartment to you.

373
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:48,640
Alright?

374
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:53,120
Don't you want
a home of your own in Weiyang?

375
00:24:56,360 --> 00:24:57,880
<i>A home of my own…</i>

376
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:00,880
<i>That offer was too tempting.</i>

377
00:25:03,280 --> 00:25:04,120
I was moved.

378
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:07,560
So I forced myself

379
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:09,880
to endure it

380
00:25:10,560 --> 00:25:11,520
and suffer through it.

381
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:15,000
That's how I lasted a whole year.

382
00:25:17,120 --> 00:25:20,080
Maybe Heaven pitied me.

383
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:22,760
At the end of 1996,

384
00:25:23,360 --> 00:25:26,280
Yao Baiyuan went up
to the 18th floor at night

385
00:25:26,360 --> 00:25:28,960
to peep at the Pattia staff

386
00:25:30,720 --> 00:25:32,280
and fell to his death.

387
00:25:34,120 --> 00:25:36,520
Qian Dajun knows everything about that.

388
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:38,920
Yao Xincheng

389
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:41,160
was a wealthy businessman
from another province.

390
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:43,320
He was in overseas trade.

391
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:46,560
His father was Yao Baiyuan.

392
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:49,480
He had a strange illness.
He couldn't stand daylight.

393
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:51,120
No one could cure it.

394
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:53,000
In 1995,

395
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:54,920
he came to Weiyang for business

396
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:58,520
and heard that the Qihuang Clinic
in our building

397
00:25:58,600 --> 00:26:00,160
specialized in rare illnesses.

398
00:26:00,240 --> 00:26:01,960
To make treatment easier,

399
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:03,200
Yao Xincheng

400
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:07,120
bought an apartment at New York Block
under Yao Baiyuan's name.

401
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:09,000
He hired a maid.

402
00:26:09,760 --> 00:26:10,840
You don't know this,

403
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:12,840
but Yao Baiyuan was a pervert.

404
00:26:13,560 --> 00:26:17,000
He had ways and means
to torment those young maids.

405
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:17,880
Be serious.

406
00:26:19,360 --> 00:26:20,280
Alright.

407
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:23,760
Well, no maid could put up with it.

408
00:26:23,840 --> 00:26:24,880
None of them lasted long.

409
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:26,760
He was changing maids every week or two.

410
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:28,160
In the end,

411
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:31,160
every maid in Weiyang
refused to work for him.

412
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:33,960
<i>Yao Xincheng could only</i>

413
00:26:34,040 --> 00:26:36,680
<i>pay high prices to hire</i>
<i>a maid from another town.</i>

414
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:41,320
How did Yao Baiyuan die?

415
00:26:42,520 --> 00:26:44,960
That pervert got himself killed.

416
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:47,120
He ran to the 18th floor to Pattia

417
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:48,960
to peep at the girls changing.

418
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:31,000
Help! Help!

419
00:27:51,080 --> 00:27:53,960
Does Yao Baiyuan's death
have anything to do with Qiao Suqing?

420
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:56,120
Probably not.

421
00:27:57,160 --> 00:27:58,920
The police came too.

422
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:00,240
His death was ruled accidental.

423
00:28:00,320 --> 00:28:02,160
Besides, whenever he went out,

424
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:03,760
he always locked Qiao Suqing inside.

425
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:06,040
After that accident,

426
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:08,200
Yao Xincheng returned from overseas.

427
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:10,880
It wasn't until after he dealt
with the funeral arrangements

428
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:13,880
that he remembered
someone was still locked inside No. 415.

429
00:28:21,160 --> 00:28:22,200
Give me a hand.

430
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:47,320
Mr. Yao was a filial son.

431
00:28:47,840 --> 00:28:49,560
He wanted to earn virtue for his father.

432
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:53,680
So he kept his promise
and transferred that apartment to me.

433
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:57,080
It was just that
he held foreign citizenship,

434
00:28:57,680 --> 00:28:59,720
and the inheritance procedures
were complicated.

435
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:02,200
So he let me live there first

436
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:06,360
and said he'd handle the paperwork
the next time he came back.

437
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:09,280
I lived there for five years.

438
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:12,560
By

439
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,760
the winter of 2002,

440
00:29:15,840 --> 00:29:17,880
he still didn't have time to come back.

441
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:19,960
I started pressing him about it.

442
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:23,160
So he mailed me all the documents

443
00:29:23,240 --> 00:29:24,240
and told me to handle it for him.

444
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:27,920
But by then, I wanted
to leave that apartment.

445
00:29:29,120 --> 00:29:30,520
So I sold it.

446
00:29:31,240 --> 00:29:34,280
Why did you buy it back in early 2003?

447
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:37,560
At the time, I was working
at an insurance company.

448
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:41,120
I dealt with a lot
of real estate developers.

449
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:46,120
They all said housing prices
in Weiyang were about to skyrocket.

450
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:49,240
Even though Yuanlongli
had rumors about a cursed building,

451
00:29:49,840 --> 00:29:51,400
and prices there wouldn't rise much,

452
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:53,080
the location was still excellent.

453
00:29:53,160 --> 00:29:55,000
If it couldn't be sold,

454
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:56,960
the owners could always wait
for demolition compensation.

455
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,160
Later, I worked hard

456
00:29:59,240 --> 00:30:01,040
to get into the demolition department
of a property company

457
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:04,080
so I could get
a bigger share of the payout.

458
00:30:05,600 --> 00:30:07,560
Why did you buy it
under Yao Xincheng's name

459
00:30:08,160 --> 00:30:09,640
and leave it untransferred
for more than ten years?

460
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:13,320
Back then, there were always rumors
in the building

461
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:16,320
that I was being kept by some rich man.

462
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:18,480
I had no way to explain it.

463
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,960
If the apartment showed under my name,

464
00:30:22,160 --> 00:30:24,240
there'd be even less way to explain it.

465
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:26,800
Qiao Suqing,

466
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:29,560
your story is touching.

467
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:33,920
But it has nothing to do with my question.

468
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:37,680
I'll repeat myself.

469
00:30:46,040 --> 00:30:48,200
How did you kill Xu Meng and her father?

470
00:30:50,320 --> 00:30:51,320
Officer He,

471
00:30:51,840 --> 00:30:53,280
I already told you.

472
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:55,040
Their deaths had nothing to do with me.

473
00:30:55,120 --> 00:30:56,840
Did you see them again

474
00:30:57,360 --> 00:30:58,880
after the Mount Wu accident?

475
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:04,640
Yes.

476
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:07,960
I saw Xu Meng.

477
00:31:11,880 --> 00:31:12,720
Scissors.

478
00:31:12,800 --> 00:31:13,720
- Drink.
- Come on.

479
00:31:13,800 --> 00:31:15,200
What are you waiting for? Drink.

480
00:31:16,520 --> 00:31:17,680
- Again.
- One more!

481
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:20,240
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

482
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:21,600
Drink.

483
00:31:30,120 --> 00:31:34,000
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

484
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:37,520
Pretending not to know me?

485
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,880
We're pretty fated

486
00:31:45,960 --> 00:31:47,840
to run into each other in Weiyang.

487
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:50,560
I came here to visit a friend.

488
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:51,840
I'm leaving tomorrow.

489
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:54,320
Lend me some money.

490
00:31:56,840 --> 00:31:57,840
I have no money.

491
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:59,080
No money?

492
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:08,960
Did you forget who you are,

493
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:11,240
murderer?

494
00:32:12,320 --> 00:32:15,000
You pushed your mom off the cliff.

495
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:17,960
Do the police know that?

496
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:25,200
Wait.

497
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:32,000
You're not staying
at a friend's place, are you?

498
00:33:26,360 --> 00:33:27,600
Nice?

499
00:33:29,400 --> 00:33:30,240
This…

500
00:33:31,240 --> 00:33:32,600
This was a gift. You can't take it.

501
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:49,040
Thanks.

502
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:04,280
<i>I had just crawled out of one living hell,</i>

503
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:08,159
<i>only to be dragged into another.</i>

504
00:34:11,639 --> 00:34:12,679
Xu Meng

505
00:34:13,440 --> 00:34:15,719
worked at Pattia on the 18th floor.

506
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:19,880
She kept knocking on my door,
asking for money.

507
00:34:19,960 --> 00:34:21,600
In the spring of 1997,

508
00:34:23,400 --> 00:34:24,960
there was a crackdown
on prostitution at Pattia.

509
00:34:25,719 --> 00:34:27,760
I thought I had finally broken free.

510
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:31,000
But instead, she came even more often,

511
00:34:31,760 --> 00:34:33,960
saying she owed loan sharks.

512
00:34:34,760 --> 00:34:36,600
I had no money to give her,

513
00:34:37,199 --> 00:34:40,280
so she started taking things from my home.

514
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:41,600
Until…

515
00:34:42,679 --> 00:34:44,600
Until I met someone.

516
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:47,679
To be precise,

517
00:34:51,639 --> 00:34:53,280
he wasn't even human.

518
00:34:59,440 --> 00:35:00,560
Hold on.

519
00:35:04,960 --> 00:35:06,120
Thank you.

520
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:21,680
Miss,

521
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:24,680
sell your stockings to me.

522
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:27,440
Name any price you want.

523
00:35:31,080 --> 00:35:32,200
I can help you take them off.

524
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:35,640
Don't come near me.

525
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:40,800
- Come on.
- Don't come near me!

526
00:35:44,680 --> 00:35:46,480
Later, I found out

527
00:35:47,160 --> 00:35:48,360
Wu Shanlong

528
00:35:49,040 --> 00:35:51,800
was the brother-in-law
of a rich businessman, Song Qingsong.

529
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:53,760
He lived on the 17th floor.

530
00:35:54,280 --> 00:35:55,400
From then on,

531
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:57,280
I hid whenever I saw him.

532
00:35:58,160 --> 00:35:59,920
But what was bound to happen

533
00:36:00,640 --> 00:36:02,560
was impossible to escape.

534
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:08,440
I heard someone

535
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:11,840
has been following you lately, right?

536
00:36:13,240 --> 00:36:16,240
A girl from the foot massage shop.

537
00:36:16,760 --> 00:36:17,960
Her name is Mengmeng.

538
00:36:19,080 --> 00:36:20,480
I can help you take care of it.

539
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:23,840
You only need to give me

540
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:25,920
a little reward.

541
00:36:32,560 --> 00:36:33,800
Miss.

542
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:37,120
Miss, once you've thought it through,

543
00:36:38,080 --> 00:36:39,800
come to me anytime.

544
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:44,320
<i>I knew what kind of man Wu Shanlong was.</i>

545
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:47,400
I didn't want to be
involved with him in any way.

546
00:36:48,880 --> 00:36:51,600
So I did nothing but stay hidden at home.

547
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:53,880
A few days later,

548
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:55,640
<i>I heard</i>

549
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:58,880
<i>Xu Meng and her father</i>
<i>had disappeared in the building.</i>

550
00:37:08,200 --> 00:37:09,520
<i>Eighteen pillars</i>

551
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:10,720
<i>with 18 men to carry them.</i>

552
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:12,040
<i>Eighteen bodies,</i>

553
00:37:12,120 --> 00:37:13,240
<i>18 heads.</i>

554
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:15,000
<i>Pass this rhyme on to three people.</i>

555
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:17,840
<i>Otherwise, calamity will befall you</i>
<i>within three days.</i>

556
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:28,560
What are you doing? Get out!

557
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:34,520
Miss,

558
00:37:35,520 --> 00:37:36,920
Mengmeng and her dad

559
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:38,520
are dead.

560
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:41,480
I killed them.

561
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:45,000
I lured them into my place

562
00:37:46,080 --> 00:37:46,960
and killed them both with one stab each.

563
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:54,920
I've already taken care of your problem.

564
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:56,640
Shouldn't you

565
00:37:57,440 --> 00:37:59,160
pay me back now?

566
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:04,760
Whatever you did
has nothing to do with me.

567
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:07,120
Get out of here,
or I'm calling the police.

568
00:38:07,640 --> 00:38:08,560
Go ahead.

569
00:38:09,160 --> 00:38:10,440
Call the police.

570
00:38:11,200 --> 00:38:13,240
About what Mengmeng told me
before she died,

571
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:16,280
I'd like to speak with the police.

572
00:38:20,920 --> 00:38:21,760
Miss,

573
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:25,720
what you did on Mount Wu,

574
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:28,160
I know all about it.

575
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:08,480
Come on.

576
00:39:09,880 --> 00:39:11,040
Give me a smile.

577
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:21,960
From then on,

578
00:39:24,680 --> 00:39:26,800
Wu Shanlong kept coming,

579
00:39:28,760 --> 00:39:31,440
asking for

580
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:32,960
worn underwear

581
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:34,560
and stockings.

582
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:41,160
It disgusted me,

583
00:39:41,240 --> 00:39:42,840
but I was too scared to fight back.

584
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:45,400
I put up with it for four or five years.

585
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:46,840
I never thought

586
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:49,280
he would go even further.

587
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:56,280
Miss,

588
00:39:56,800 --> 00:39:58,560
whatever you do at home,

589
00:39:58,640 --> 00:40:00,560
act natural like before.

590
00:40:01,080 --> 00:40:02,360
Don't avoid the camera

591
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:05,480
or close the curtains.

592
00:40:05,560 --> 00:40:07,680
Not even when you sleep.

593
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:18,920
Cheer up, miss.

594
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:25,080
<i>All I wanted was to crawl</i>
<i>out of the abyss,</i>

595
00:40:25,600 --> 00:40:27,200
<i>to see the light,</i>

596
00:40:28,080 --> 00:40:29,440
<i>and hold onto it.</i>

597
00:40:34,360 --> 00:40:37,040
<i>Someone always dragged me back down.</i>

598
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:42,760
During that time,

599
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:48,600
I thought about killing myself
more than once.

600
00:40:50,520 --> 00:40:51,720
Later,

601
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:53,280
Xu Zhihong's severed head

602
00:40:53,360 --> 00:40:55,520
was found on the rooftop.

603
00:40:57,400 --> 00:40:58,400
That's when I found out

604
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:04,040
Wu Shanlong hadn't just killed
Xu Meng and her father,

605
00:41:05,800 --> 00:41:07,840
he had dismembered them too.

606
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:12,080
I was so terrified,
I couldn't sleep for days.

607
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:14,120
I was scared that one day,

608
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:16,040
I would end up just like them.

609
00:41:16,840 --> 00:41:18,120
So I thought

610
00:41:18,720 --> 00:41:21,480
I had to break free
from Wu Shanlong's control.

611
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:24,280
I had to make that murderer pay
for what he did.

612
00:41:25,600 --> 00:41:27,640
Wu Shanlong had a fetish.

613
00:41:27,720 --> 00:41:30,160
He stole clothes
from women in the building.

614
00:41:31,040 --> 00:41:32,640
So I went to a secondhand shop

615
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:37,760
and found a pair of heels
the same style Xu Meng took from me.

616
00:41:37,840 --> 00:41:40,080
But they only had red.

617
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:43,040
I had no friends in Weiyang,

618
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:45,640
so I paid

619
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:47,720
Yao Xincheng's driver

620
00:41:48,360 --> 00:41:50,000
to have them changed to blue.

621
00:42:13,400 --> 00:42:14,360
Those shoes,

622
00:42:15,240 --> 00:42:16,400
I want them too.

623
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:23,560
I'm not taking them off in the hallway.

624
00:42:52,640 --> 00:42:55,800
Miss, you're a curious cat.

625
00:42:59,040 --> 00:43:00,400
I have something

626
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:02,560
more wild.

627
00:43:05,800 --> 00:43:06,760
Want to see?

628
00:43:21,400 --> 00:43:22,240
Come on.

629
00:43:24,520 --> 00:43:25,520
Come on.

630
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:39,360
I believe you know

631
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:42,840
what happened after that.

632
00:44:44,160 --> 00:44:46,160
That's the whole truth.

633
00:44:47,120 --> 00:44:48,960
I did hate Xu Meng,

634
00:44:50,120 --> 00:44:52,040
but I didn't kill her or her father.

635
00:44:52,680 --> 00:44:53,520
Instead,

636
00:44:57,080 --> 00:44:58,400
I was a victim too.

637
00:45:01,160 --> 00:45:02,360
Your story is flawless.

638
00:45:06,920 --> 00:45:08,320
This whole explanation,

639
00:45:08,400 --> 00:45:10,520
you must've planned for years, didn't you?
